# Project Context Verification

Fairfield Polo Club website: Next.js storefront on Vercel with Sanity CMS,
Medusa commerce, Resend, Mailchimp, and Behold Instagram.

Before any GitHub admin, Vercel deploy/env, Cloudflare DNS, Sanity project,
Medusa production, secret, or production data operation:

1. Run `make doctor` from `~/projects/FairfieldPolo`.
2. Stop if any doctor check fails.
3. Report all warnings.
4. State the intended target and operation.
5. Classify the operation as read-only, create, modify, or delete.
6. Wait for explicit approval before any create, modify, or delete action.

## Fixed project boundaries

- GitHub account: set in `.env.infrastructure.local` (`PROJECT_GITHUB_ACCOUNT`)
- GitHub org/repo: `FairfieldPolo/FairfieldPoloWebsite`
- Workspace: `~/projects/FairfieldPolo`
- Public site: `https://fairfieldpolo.com`
- Deploy target: Vercel
- DNS: Cloudflare zone `fairfieldpolo.com` (apex/www → Vercel; typically DNS-only)
- CMS: Sanity (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID` / dataset)
- Commerce: Medusa Store API (separate backend; not in this repo)
- Email: Resend (contact) + Mailchimp (newsletter)
- Instagram: Behold.so widget

This is **not** a Darrah Oil or PostRock Ag workspace. Do not use those Azure
profiles, Unraid aliases, or their Cloudflare zones (`darrahoil.com` /
`postrockag.com`) here.

If `make doctor` fails, do not attempt to switch accounts or repair the
context automatically.
